<qti-assessment-item xmlns="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0" xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" identifier="Q27_v7" title="Q27_v7" time-dependent="false" adaptive="false" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0 https://purl.imsglobal.org/spec/qti/v3p0/schema/xsd/imsqti_asiv3p0_v1p0.xsd">
  <qti-response-declaration identifier="RESPONSE" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier">
    <qti-correct-response>
      <qti-value>ChoiceB</qti-value>
    </qti-correct-response>
  </qti-response-declaration>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="FEEDBACK" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SOLUTION" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SCORE" cardinality="single" base-type="float"><qti-default-value><qti-value>0</qti-value></qti-default-value></qti-outcome-declaration><qti-item-body>
    <p>El área A(x), en metros cuadrados, de un rectángulo se expresa en función de x como:</p>
    <p>
      <m:math>
        <m:mi>A</m:mi><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>)</m:mo>
        <m:mo>=</m:mo>
        <m:msup><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msup>
        <m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>9</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi>
        <m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>20</m:mn>
      </m:math>
    </p>
    <p>Si el largo y el ancho del rectángulo se expresan como binomios de la forma (x + a) y (x + b), ¿cuál de las siguientes parejas de expresiones podría representar sus dimensiones?</p>
    <qti-choice-interaction response-identifier="RESPONSE" shuffle="false" max-choices="1">
      
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceA">
        <m:math>
          <m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>4</m:mn><m:mo>)</m:mo>
          <m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>5</m:mn><m:mo>)</m:mo>
        </m:math>
        <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceA" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Al desarrollar esta expresión se obtiene (x + 4)(x + 5) = x² + 5x + 4x + 20 = x² + 9x + 20, que no coincide con x² − 9x + 20.</qti-feedback-inline>
      </qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceB">
        <m:math>
          <m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>4</m:mn><m:mo>)</m:mo>
          <m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>5</m:mn><m:mo>)</m:mo>
        </m:math>
        <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceB" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">¡Correcto! Al desarrollar esta expresión se obtiene (x − 4)(x − 5) = x² − 5x − 4x + 20 = x² − 9x + 20, exactamente la expresión dada para el área.</qti-feedback-inline>
      </qti-simple-choice>
      
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceC">
        <m:math>
          <m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mo>)</m:mo>
          <m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>7</m:mn><m:mo>)</m:mo>
        </m:math>
        <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceC" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Al desarrollar esta expresión se obtiene (x − 2)(x − 7) = x² − 7x − 2x + 14 = x² − 9x + 14. El término independiente es 14 y no 20.</qti-feedback-inline>
      </qti-simple-choice>
      
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceD">
        <m:math>
          <m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mo>)</m:mo>
          <m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>10</m:mn><m:mo>)</m:mo>
        </m:math>
        <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceD" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Al desarrollar esta expresión se obtiene (x − 2)(x − 10) = x² − 10x − 2x + 20 = x² − 12x + 20, que no coincide con x² − 9x + 20.</qti-feedback-inline>
      </qti-simple-choice>
    </qti-choice-interaction>
    <qti-feedback-block identifier="show" outcome-identifier="SOLUTION" show-hide="show">
      <qti-content-body>
        <p><strong>Resolución paso a paso por factorización</strong></p>
        <ol>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 1: Identificar la expresión del área</strong></p>
            <p>La función dada es:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mi>A</m:mi><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>)</m:mo>
                <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                <m:msup><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msup>
                <m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>9</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi>
                <m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>20</m:mn>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>Se busca escribir esta expresión como producto de dos binomios que representen largo y ancho.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 2: Recordar cómo se factoriza un trinomio de la forma</strong></p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:msup><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msup>
                <m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mi>b</m:mi><m:mi>x</m:mi>
                <m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mi>c</m:mi>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>Se necesitan dos números que al multiplicarse den 20 y al sumarse den −9.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 3: Buscar los números</strong></p>
            <p>Los pares de factores de 20 son 1 y 20, 2 y 10, 4 y 5.</p>
            <p>Como la suma debe ser −9 y el producto debe ser positivo, ambos números deben ser negativos.</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>4</m:mn><m:mo>)</m:mo>
                <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                <m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>5</m:mn><m:mo>)</m:mo>
                <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                <m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>9</m:mn>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>4</m:mn><m:mo>)</m:mo>
                <m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>5</m:mn><m:mo>)</m:mo>
                <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                <m:mn>20</m:mn>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>Por lo tanto, la factorización correcta es:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:msup><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msup>
                <m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>9</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi>
                <m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>20</m:mn>
                <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                <m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>4</m:mn><m:mo>)</m:mo>
                <m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>5</m:mn><m:mo>)</m:mo>
              </m:math>
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 4: Verificar desarrollando</strong></p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>4</m:mn><m:mo>)</m:mo>
                <m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>5</m:mn><m:mo>)</m:mo>
                <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                <m:msup><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msup>
                <m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>5</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi>
                <m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>4</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi>
                <m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>20</m:mn>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                <m:msup><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msup>
                <m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>9</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi>
                <m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>20</m:mn>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>Coincide exactamente con la función dada.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Conclusión</strong></p>
            <p>La pareja de expresiones que podría representar las dimensiones del rectángulo es la alternativa B.</p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </qti-content-body>
    </qti-feedback-block>
  </qti-item-body>
  <qti-response-processing>
    <qti-response-condition>
      <qti-response-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SCORE">
          <qti-base-value base-type="float">1</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else>
    </qti-response-condition>
  </qti-response-processing>
</qti-assessment-item>